data.value: The Dream11 Indian Premier League-2020, also known as IPL 13 was held in United Arab Emirates. The tournament was scheduled to commence on 29 March 2020, but was suspended due to the global coronavirus pandemic. Later, it was announced that the tournament would be played between 19 September and 10 November 2020. Mumbai Indians, the defending champions, won the Tournament after defeating Delhi Capitals by 5 wickets. So, here's a quick summary of IPL-2020.
